All 6 tests pass. Here's a summary of what was done:

**Bug:** Off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts`, line 7.

```ts
// Before (buggy) — stops one iteration too early
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// After (fixed) — processes all elements including the last
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

The `- 1` in the upper bound caused the loop to stop before reaching the last index, silently skipping the final element for any non-empty array. Removing it fixes the behavior, and all 6 tests now pass (4 for `processItems` + 2 for `sum`).

